{"lemma":"عَفْوٌ","slug":"عَفْوٌ","root":"ع.ف.#","root_slug":"ع-ف-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ف-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَفْو","root":"عفو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29779"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَفَا (ʕafā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pardon, forgiveness, remission of sins, amnesty, absolution"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"remitting much, clement, inclined to frequent pardon","examples":[{"text":"إِنْ تُبْدُوا خَيْرًا أَوْ تُخْفُوهُ أَوْ تَعْفُوا عَنْ سُوءٍ فَإِنَّ اللَّٰهَ كَانَ عَفُوًّا قَدِيرًا"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕafw/","/ʕa.fuww/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29779","headword_ar":"عَفْوٌ","root":"Efw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[an inf. n.; for which see 1, throughout.       -A2-  And also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land in which is no sign of the way nor trace of habitation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivation; untrodden, and not having in it any traces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vestiges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"footprints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of land, in which is no trace of its being possessed by any one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafFA","text_ar":"عَفًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A redundant portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K,) being such as is left, (Mgh,) of property,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining over and above what is expended."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) A poet says, [app. addressing his wife,]"},{"kind":"quote","text":"xu*iY AlEafowa min~iY tasotadiymiY mawad~atiY\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA tanoTiqiY fiY saworatiY Hiyna A^agoDabu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou what is redundant from me, seeking the continuance of my affection; and speak not in my fit of irritation, when I am angry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quli AlEafowa","text_ar":"قُلِ العَفْوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [ii. 217], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Say thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"Expend ye"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is redundant and abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudi AlEafowa","text_ar":"خُدِ العَفْوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the same [vii. 198]. means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accept thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is redundant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accept thou what is easily obtained from the dispositions of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and oppose them not, for in that case they would oppose thee, and thence would be engendered hatred and enmity. (TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotuhu Eafowa AlmaAli","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُهُ عَفْوَ المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him, of the property, that for which he did not ask;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spontaneously;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without being asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTayotuhu EafowFA","text_ar":"اَعْطَيْتُهُ عَفْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gave him spontaneously;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without being asked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without constraint."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraka AlA^amora EafowFA","text_ar":"اَدْرَكَ الاَمْرَ عَفْوًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attained the thing easily."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAniY *`lika","text_ar":"اَتَانِى ذٰلِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowFA","text_ar":"عَفْوًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That came to me easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gmD","text_ar":"غمض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that remains over and above what is required by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriyap","text_ar":"شَارِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which may mean either the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people that dwell thereby and to whom it belongs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinkers"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is taken without constraint and without crowding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most lawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHal~u","text_ar":"اَحَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) so in the copies of the K, but in the M"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajomalu","text_ar":"اَجْمَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodly"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and most pleasant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wealth, or property: (M, K, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clear portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"choice, and best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, portion"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing, (K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is not attended with fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weariness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneficence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a benefit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefaction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEorwfN","text_ar":"مَعْروفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A first run:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says of a courser,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowK waEaqibK","text_ar":"عَفْوٍ وَعَقِبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a first run, and a subsequent, and more vehement, ran."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqb","text_ar":"عقب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EufowN","text_ar":"عُفْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EifowN","text_ar":"عِفْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A young ass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafFA","text_ar":"عَفًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or, accord. to ISk, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EifFA","text_ar":"عِفًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the female is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowapN","text_ar":"عَفْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EifaAwapN","text_ar":"عِفَاوَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. [of mult.], accord. to the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowapN","text_ar":"عَفْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but correctly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EifawapN","text_ar":"عِفَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said by ISd to be the only instance of a word with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a final radical movent after a fet-hah, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EifaA='N","text_ar":"عِفَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, K, TA,) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEofaA='N","text_ar":"اَعْفَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISd, TA:) and [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlEifaA='i","text_ar":"اَبُو العِفَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the father of the young asses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEfaA='","text_ar":"العفَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"being pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowN","text_ar":"عَفْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young ass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","K","TA","M","ISd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}